node.text:
FOR UNILATERAL DECISION-MAKING AND BOTCHED AFGHAN WITHDRAWAL 

President Trump never drew the level of criticism on display yesterday from the U.K. Parliament,  who angrily aligned from across the political aisles to hold Joe Biden in contempt for his unilateral withdrawal from Afghanistan without discussing the issues with NATO.

According to British media,  Joe Biden would not take the calls from U.K. Prime Minister Boris Johnson for 36 hours as the crisis unfolded.  The British and allied forces were scrambling to secure their own troops and diplomats with no guidance or contact from the White House.

Labour and Conservative parties expressed a united anger and frustration toward a failed and inept U.S. administration.

Notice at the end he does not mention the United States. They have zero trust in America at this point. Sad 😢

node.title: BRITISH PARLIAMENT HOLD JOE BIDEN IN CONTEMPT

node.text:
If you haven’t heard this radio transmission, please take the time to listen. ⛔️Be cautioned it is hard to listen to.⛔️

The calm voice in the chaos  in Chicago during the incident that occurred on 8/7/2021. Thank you Dispatcher Keith Thornton - The way he took control of this incident and talked to his officers, kept his air completely shut down and clear, set a perimeter within seconds quite possibly is what resulted in the apprehension of the suspects. 

Dispatcher Keith Thornton was fast thinking and took initiative without any direction in the very beginning stages and ran the emergency like an actual incident commander - far beyond the criteria of any dispatcher. 

The world heard you loud and clear and we stand with you. 💙🖤💙🖤💙🖤💙
#chicago #dispatcherlife #policedispatcher #bluelivesmatter #chicagopolicedepartment #keiththorton #policeofficer #police #lawenforcement

node.text:
After COVID-Stricken Migrants Seen ‘Coughing, Sneezing’ at a Restaurant. 

HIDALGO COUNTY, Texas (CBSDFW.COM) – The La Joya Police Department issued a public health announcement after an officer approached an undocumented migrant family at Whataburger who told him Border Patrol released them because they had COVID-19.

On July 26 the police department of the small town along the Rio Grande and Mexican border shared details of the incident. They said a concerned citizen at the restaurant waved down the officer. The citizen told him about the family “coughing and sneezing without covering their mouths and not wearing face masks.” Whataburger management also told the officer that they wanted the group to leave as well due to “their disregard to other people’s health.”

According to British media,  Joe Biden would not take the calls from U.K. Prime Minister Boris Johnson for 36 hours as the crisis unfolded.  The British and allied forces were scrambling to secure their own troops and diplomats with no guidance or contact from the White House.

Labour and Conservative parties expressed a united anger and frustration toward a failed and inept U.S. administration.

node.text:
“This is what it looks like outside the north gate at the airport in Kabul. I won't mention why this location is important. I will say that the CENTCOM commander, who agreed to allow this airport to be the primary/only evacuation point, should be dismissed/replaced immediately.” ~ Bill Roggio, a former soldier and senior fellow at the Foundation for Defense of Democracies. @ billroggio twitter 

“This is incompetence of the highest order. If you are a congressman or senator and you care about this country, stand up now, and demand the cancer that is within our general officer corps be cut out.” ~ @ billroggio twittter 

Abandoning Bagram air base before withdrawing American civilians and Afghan allies was a major tactical mistake, according to senior national security experts, leaving U.S. forces reliant on a civilian airport, with a single runway in the heart of a city controlled by the Taliban.

They said days of chaos could have been avoided if the U.S. evacuation plan included Bagram, 25 miles to the north.

“"KIA" indeed. To be clear, General Milley, the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff "approved" the proposal by  CENTCOM Gen. McKenzie & then @USFOR_A Gen. Miller to shut down Bagram and rely on Kabul airport. Hold them accountable. Milley and McKenzie should resign or be fired.”

“They never saw it coming. They never understood what was happening even while it was happening. They had zero imagination & couldn't conceive of the possibility that the house of cards which they helped build on a bed of sand might actually collapse. How did I know & they didn't?” ~ source @ billroggio twitter

node.text:
JUST IN: The reason Joe Biden's Afghanistan evacuation is failing so badly is because the Biden Admin ordered the State Dept to halt President Trump's 'Crisis Response Bureau’ aimed at avoiding Benghazi-style evacuations just MONTHS before the Taliban takeover.

The “Contingency and Crisis Response Bureau” – was designed to handle medical, diplomatic, and logistical support concerning Americans overseas

“Canceling this successful [Trump] program before the withdrawal that would have helped tens of thousands Americans reach home is beyond disgraceful. Our withdrawal was conditions-based and perfect...nobody would have even known we left.”
-President Trump

node.text:
BAGRAM, Afghanistan (AP) — The U.S. left Afghanistan’s Bagram Airfield after nearly 20 years by shutting off the electricity and slipping away in the night without notifying the base’s new Afghan commander, who discovered the Americans’ departure more than two hours after they left, Afghan military officials said.

Before the Afghan army could take control of the airfield about an hour’s drive from the Afghan capital Kabul, it was invaded by a small army of looters, who ransacked barrack after barrack and rummaged through giant storage tents before being evicted, according to Afghan military officials.

Just look at all of that Military equipment left behind; all our Tax Dollars just abandoned. What was Joe Biden thinking? 🙄

This is another example of the catastrophic failures by the Biden Administration. They didn’t tell anyone in the Afghan Military they were abandoning the base, according to Afghan Military Officials. If true this is another MASSIVE catastrophic failure by the Biden Administration 🙄
